      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">3-Methyl-1-butyl acetate is prepared by the esterification of isoamyl alcohol with acetic acid. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">The reaction of an alcohol and an organic acid produces an ester in the presence of an acid catalyst.  Commercial processes for esterification are continuous and are performed in the liquid phase. The reaction requires sulfuric acid. Esterification involves an equilibrium between reactants and product. Adding excess reactants or removal of water drives the equilibrium to favor the formation of ester. Azeotroping agents eliminate water and force the reaction to completion. Common agents are cyclohexane, benzene, and toluene.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Gräfje, H., Körnig, W., Weitz, H.-M., Reiß, W.: Butanediols, Butenediol, and Butynediol, Chapter 1. In: Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Sev-enth Edition, 2004 Electronic Release (ed. Fiedler E., Grossmann G., Kersebohm D., Weiss G. and Witte C.). 7 th Electronic Release Edition. WileyInterScience, New York, Online-Version under:  http://www.mrw.interscience.wiley.com/ueic/articles/a04_455/frame.html</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="1989-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Time of publications</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
    <flowData>
      <intermediateExchange id="0407a423-9f70-5fee-ad90-e7244aff7a1c" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="123-92-2" amount="1.0" intermediateExchangeId="ef84c866-e125-4835-8747-ed684e87d36e" productionVolumeAmount="1.32236940655721">
        <name xml:lang="en">3-methyl-1-butyl acetate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">3-Methyl-1-butyl acetate is a liquid with a strong fruity odor that has been identified in many fruit aromas.  It is the main component of banana aromas and is, therefore, also used in banana flavors.  It can be found in foods, candy, butter, coconut, cola, rum, as a flavor for paint and insecticides and as a solvent.
EcoSpold01Location=RER</comment>
